# v0.5.4 CI coverage-floor bump — maintainer-applied patch
#
# The v0.5.4 "honesty sweep" raised `[tool.coverage.report] fail_under`
# from 80 → 82 in `pyproject.toml` to match the 82.11% lived floor
# published by the README TEST-BADGE block. Local `pytest` runs already
# pick this up.
#
# The companion change to `.github/workflows/ci.yml` requires the
# `workflow` OAuth scope to push, so automated PRs cannot apply it.
# A maintainer must open `.github/workflows/ci.yml` and change the one
# line shown below by hand (line number may drift; match by context).
#
# Before:
#           pytest tests/ -v --cov=agent_airlock --cov-report=xml --cov-report=term-missing --cov-fail-under=80
#
# After:
#           pytest tests/ -v --cov=agent_airlock --cov-report=xml --cov-report=term-missing --cov-fail-under=82
#
# Until applied, CI enforces a floor 2 points below `pyproject.toml`.
# Drift is harmless but wasteful; apply the one-line change on the next
# maintainer commit.
